{
  "video_id": "y9Trdafp83U",
  "title": "There's more to life than being happy | Emily Esfahani Smith",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12724.0,
      "end_time": 14300.0,
      "text": "I used to think"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14270.0,
      "end_time": 17761.0,
      "text": "the whole purpose of life was pursuing happiness."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18500.0,
      "end_time": 21884.0,
      "text": "Everyone said the path to happiness was success,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21908.0,
      "end_time": 24406.0,
      "text": "so I searched for that ideal job,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24430.0,
      "end_time": 27461.0,
      "text": "that perfect boyfriend, that beautiful apartment."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 28818.0,
      "end_time": 31816.0,
      "text": "But instead of ever feeling fulfilled,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31840.0,
      "end_time": 34444.0,
      "text": "I felt anxious and adrift."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35150.0,
      "end_time": 39240.0,
      "text": "And I wasn&#39;t alone; my friends -- they struggled with this, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 40540.0,
      "end_time": 44809.0,
      "text": "Eventually, I decided to go to graduate school for positive psychology"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 44833.0,
      "end_time": 48530.0,
      "text": "to learn what truly makes people happy."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 48791.0,
      "end_time": 51446.0,
      "text": "But what I discovered there changed my life."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 52272.0,
      "end_time": 56882.0,
      "text": "The data showed that chasing happiness can make people unhappy."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 57787.0,
      "end_time": 60440.0,
      "text": "And what really struck me was this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 60878.0,
      "end_time": 63665.0,
      "text": "the suicide rate has been rising around the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 63689.0,
      "end_time": 66780.0,
      "text": "and it recently reached a 30-year high in America."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 67573.0,
      "end_time": 70336.0,
      "text": "Even though life is getting objectively better"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 70360.0,
      "end_time": 73500.0,
      "text": "by nearly every conceivable standard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 73740.0,
      "end_time": 75273.0,
      "text": "more people feel hopeless,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 75297.0,
      "end_time": 77422.0,
      "text": "depressed and alone."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 78340.0,
      "end_time": 80847.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s an emptiness gnawing away at people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 80871.0,
      "end_time": 84140.0,
      "text": "and you don&#39;t have to be clinically depressed to feel it."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 84165.0,
      "end_time": 87650.0,
      "text": "Sooner or later, I think we all wonder:"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 87604.0,
      "end_time": 89836.0,
      "text": "Is this all there is?"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 90987.0,
      "end_time": 94193.0,
      "text": "And according to the research, what predicts this despair"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 94217.0,
      "end_time": 96440.0,
      "text": "is not a lack of happiness."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 96680.0,
      "end_time": 97910.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a lack of something else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 98637.0,
      "end_time": 101575.0,
      "text": "a lack of having meaning in life."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 102782.0,
      "end_time": 105175.0,
      "text": "But that raised some questions for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 105675.0,
      "end_time": 108274.0,
      "text": "Is there more to life than being happy?"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 109360.0,
      "end_time": 111459.0,
      "text": "And what&#39;s the difference between being happy"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 111483.0,
      "end_time": 113374.0,
      "text": "and having meaning in life?"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 114699.0,
      "end_time": 119298.0,
      "text": "Many psychologists define happiness as a state of comfort and ease,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 119323.0,
      "end_time": 121211.0,
      "text": "feeling good in the moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 121918.0,
      "end_time": 123576.0,
      "text": "Meaning, though, is deeper."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 124980.0,
      "end_time": 126662.0,
      "text": "The renowned psychologist Martin Seligman says"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 126686.0,
      "end_time": 131333.0,
      "text": "meaning comes from belonging to and serving something beyond yourself"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 131357.0,
      "end_time": 134400.0,
      "text": "and from developing the best within you."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 135437.0,
      "end_time": 138320.0,
      "text": "Our culture is obsessed with happiness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 138560.0,
      "end_time": 142163.0,
      "text": "but I came to see that seeking meaning is the more fulfilling path."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 142187.0,
      "end_time": 145116.0,
      "text": "And the studies show that people who have meaning in life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 145140.0,
      "end_time": 146549.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re more resilient,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 146574.0,
      "end_time": 149131.0,
      "text": "they do better in school and at work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 149155.0,
      "end_time": 150762.0,
      "text": "and they even live longer."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 151805.0,
      "end_time": 153826.0,
      "text": "So this all made me wonder:"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 153850.0,
      "end_time": 156323.0,
      "text": "How can we each live more meaningfully?"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 157800.0,
      "end_time": 161478.0,
      "text": "To find out, I spent five years interviewing hundreds of people"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 161502.0,
      "end_time": 164403.0,
      "text": "and reading through thousands of pages of psychology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 164427.0,
      "end_time": 166528.0,
      "text": "neuroscience and philosophy."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 167186.0,
      "end_time": 168975.0,
      "text": "Bringing it all together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 168999.0,
      "end_time": 174340.0,
      "text": "I found that there are what I call four pillars of a meaningful life."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 174364.0,
      "end_time": 176798.0,
      "text": "And we can each create lives of meaning"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 176822.0,
      "end_time": 180171.0,
      "text": "by building some or all of these pillars in our lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 181248.0,
      "end_time": 183435.0,
      "text": "The first pillar is belonging."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 184198.0,
      "end_time": 186505.0,
      "text": "Belonging comes from being in relationships"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 186529.0,
      "end_time": 189234.0,
      "text": "where you&#39;re valued for who you are intrinsically"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 189258.0,
      "end_time": 191371.0,
      "text": "and where you value others as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 192380.0,
      "end_time": 196728.0,
      "text": "But some groups and relationships deliver a cheap form of belonging;"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 196752.0,
      "end_time": 198645.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re valued for what you believe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 198669.0,
      "end_time": 199915.0,
      "text": "for who you hate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 199939.0,
      "end_time": 201483.0,
      "text": "not for who you are."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 202240.0,
      "end_time": 205230.0,
      "text": "True belonging springs from love."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 205470.0,
      "end_time": 208320.0,
      "text": "It lives in moments among individuals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 208560.0,
      "end_time": 211901.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s a choice -- you can choose to cultivate belonging with others."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 212481.0,
      "end_time": 214880.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s an example."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 214112.0,
      "end_time": 217667.0,
      "text": "Each morning, my friend Jonathan buys a newspaper"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 217691.0,
      "end_time": 219909.0,
      "text": "from the same street vendor in New York."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 220322.0,
      "end_time": 222602.0,
      "text": "They don&#39;t just conduct a transaction, though."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 222626.0,
      "end_time": 225309.0,
      "text": "They take a moment to slow down, talk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 225333.0,
      "end_time": 227239.0,
      "text": "and treat each other like humans."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 227858.0,
      "end_time": 231252.0,
      "text": "But one time, Jonathan didn&#39;t have the right change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 231276.0,
      "end_time": 232496.0,
      "text": "and the vendor said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 232520.0,
      "end_time": 234400.0,
      "text": "\"Don&#39;t worry about it.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 234640.0,
      "end_time": 236551.0,
      "text": "But Jonathan insisted on paying,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 236575.0,
      "end_time": 239587.0,
      "text": "so he went to the store and bought something he didn&#39;t need"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 239611.0,
      "end_time": 241720.0,
      "text": "to make change."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 241812.0,
      "end_time": 244435.0,
      "text": "But when he gave the money to the vendor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 244459.0,
      "end_time": 245981.0,
      "text": "the vendor drew back."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 246640.0,
      "end_time": 247917.0,
      "text": "He was hurt."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 248535.0,
      "end_time": 250384.0,
      "text": "He was trying to do something kind,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 250408.0,
      "end_time": 252654.0,
      "text": "but Jonathan had rejected him."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 253933.0,
      "end_time": 258840.0,
      "text": "I think we all reject people in small ways like this without realizing it."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 258108.0,
      "end_time": 259305.0,
      "text": "I do."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 259329.0,
      "end_time": 262393.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll walk by someone I know and barely acknowledge them."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 262417.0,
      "end_time": 265630.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll check my phone when someone&#39;s talking to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 265498.0,
      "end_time": 267426.0,
      "text": "These acts devalue others."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 267451.0,
      "end_time": 270204.0,
      "text": "They make them feel invisible and unworthy."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 270950.0,
      "end_time": 273702.0,
      "text": "But when you lead with love, you create a bond"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 273726.0,
      "end_time": 275398.0,
      "text": "that lifts each of you up."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 276850.0,
      "end_time": 280478.0,
      "text": "For many people, belonging is the most essential source of meaning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 280502.0,
      "end_time": 282500.0,
      "text": "those bonds to family and friends."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 282996.0,
      "end_time": 287100.0,
      "text": "For others, the key to meaning is the second pillar: purpose."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 287664.0,
      "end_time": 290579.0,
      "text": "Now, finding your purpose is not the same thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 290603.0,
      "end_time": 292851.0,
      "text": "as finding that job that makes you happy."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 293340.0,
      "end_time": 296799.0,
      "text": "Purpose is less about what you want than about what you give."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 296823.0,
      "end_time": 301311.0,
      "text": "A hospital custodian told me her purpose is healing sick people."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 301335.0,
      "end_time": 303460.0,
      "text": "Many parents tell me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 303700.0,
      "end_time": 305600.0,
      "text": "\"My purpose is raising my children.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 305347.0,
      "end_time": 309390.0,
      "text": "The key to purpose is using your strengths to serve others."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 310201.0,
      "end_time": 313709.0,
      "text": "Of course, for many of us, that happens through work."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 313733.0,
      "end_time": 316712.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s how we contribute and feel needed."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 316736.0,
      "end_time": 320596.0,
      "text": "But that also means that issues like disengagement at work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 320620.0,
      "end_time": 322330.0,
      "text": "unemployment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 322570.0,
      "end_time": 324284.0,
      "text": "low labor force participation --"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 324308.0,
      "end_time": 327998.0,
      "text": "these aren&#39;t just economic problems, they&#39;re existential ones, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 328641.0,
      "end_time": 330854.0,
      "text": "Without something worthwhile to do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 330878.0,
      "end_time": 332179.0,
      "text": "people flounder."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 333313.0,
      "end_time": 335929.0,
      "text": "Of course, you don&#39;t have to find purpose at work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 335953.0,
      "end_time": 338681.0,
      "text": "but purpose gives you something to live for,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 338706.0,
      "end_time": 340786.0,
      "text": "some \"why\" that drives you forward."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 342967.0,
      "end_time": 346267.0,
      "text": "The third pillar of meaning is also about stepping beyond yourself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 346291.0,
      "end_time": 348133.0,
      "text": "but in a completely different way:"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 348157.0,
      "end_time": 349744.0,
      "text": "transcendence."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 349768.0,
      "end_time": 352145.0,
      "text": "Transcendent states are those rare moments"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 352169.0,
      "end_time": 355580.0,
      "text": "when you&#39;re lifted above the hustle and bustle of daily life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 355605.0,
      "end_time": 357310.0,
      "text": "your sense of self fades away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 357334.0,
      "end_time": 360108.0,
      "text": "and you feel connected to a higher reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 361340.0,
      "end_time": 364724.0,
      "text": "For one person I talked to, transcendence came from seeing art."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 364748.0,
      "end_time": 367277.0,
      "text": "For another person, it was at church."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 367302.0,
      "end_time": 370856.0,
      "text": "For me, I&#39;m a writer, and it happens through writing."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 370880.0,
      "end_time": 375950.0,
      "text": "Sometimes I get so in the zone that I lose all sense of time and place."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 376577.0,
      "end_time": 379723.0,
      "text": "These transcendent experiences can change you."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 379747.0,
      "end_time": 384271.0,
      "text": "One study had students look up at 200-feet-tall eucalyptus trees"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 384295.0,
      "end_time": 385496.0,
      "text": "for one minute."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 386830.0,
      "end_time": 388237.0,
      "text": "But afterwards they felt less self-centered,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 388261.0,
      "end_time": 390205.0,
      "text": "and they even behaved more generously"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 390229.0,
      "end_time": 392299.0,
      "text": "when given the chance to help someone."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 393402.0,
      "end_time": 397122.0,
      "text": "Belonging, purpose, transcendence."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 398194.0,
      "end_time": 400917.0,
      "text": "Now, the fourth pillar of meaning, I&#39;ve found,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 400941.0,
      "end_time": 402695.0,
      "text": "tends to surprise people."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 403186.0,
      "end_time": 405919.0,
      "text": "The fourth pillar is storytelling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 405944.0,
      "end_time": 408809.0,
      "text": "the story you tell yourself about yourself."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 409436.0,
      "end_time": 413580.0,
      "text": "Creating a narrative from the events of your life brings clarity."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 413604.0,
      "end_time": 416640.0,
      "text": "It helps you understand how you became you."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 417489.0,
      "end_time": 420585.0,
      "text": "But we don&#39;t always realize that we&#39;re the authors of our stories"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 420609.0,
      "end_time": 422772.0,
      "text": "and can change the way we&#39;re telling them."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 422796.0,
      "end_time": 425287.0,
      "text": "Your life isn&#39;t just a list of events."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 425311.0,
      "end_time": 428527.0,
      "text": "You can edit, interpret and retell your story,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 428551.0,
      "end_time": 430771.0,
      "text": "even as you&#39;re constrained by the facts."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 431501.0,
      "end_time": 436128.0,
      "text": "I met a young man named Emeka, who&#39;d been paralyzed playing football."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 436740.0,
      "end_time": 439199.0,
      "text": "After his injury, Emeka told himself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 439223.0,
      "end_time": 441928.0,
      "text": "\"My life was great playing football,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 441952.0,
      "end_time": 444760.0,
      "text": "but now look at me.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 445822.0,
      "end_time": 448114.0,
      "text": "People who tell stories like this --"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 448138.0,
      "end_time": 450662.0,
      "text": "\"My life was good. Now it&#39;s bad.\" --"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 450686.0,
      "end_time": 453508.0,
      "text": "tend to be more anxious and depressed."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 453532.0,
      "end_time": 455861.0,
      "text": "And that was Emeka for a while."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 456393.0,
      "end_time": 459784.0,
      "text": "But with time, he started to weave a different story."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 460235.0,
      "end_time": 461968.0,
      "text": "His new story was,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 461992.0,
      "end_time": 465259.0,
      "text": "\"Before my injury, my life was purposeless."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 465283.0,
      "end_time": 468536.0,
      "text": "I partied a lot and was a pretty selfish guy."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 468560.0,
      "end_time": 472268.0,
      "text": "But my injury made me realize I could be a better man.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 473308.0,
      "end_time": 476849.0,
      "text": "That edit to his story changed Emeka&#39;s life."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 476873.0,
      "end_time": 479304.0,
      "text": "After telling the new story to himself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 479328.0,
      "end_time": 481250.0,
      "text": "Emeka started mentoring kids,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 481274.0,
      "end_time": 483640.0,
      "text": "and he discovered what his purpose was:"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 483664.0,
      "end_time": 485540.0,
      "text": "serving others."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 485921.0,
      "end_time": 489299.0,
      "text": "The psychologist Dan McAdams calls this a \"redemptive story,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 489323.0,
      "end_time": 491606.0,
      "text": "where the bad is redeemed by the good."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 492447.0,
      "end_time": 494630.0,
      "text": "People leading meaningful lives, he&#39;s found,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 494654.0,
      "end_time": 496585.0,
      "text": "tend to tell stories about their lives"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 496609.0,
      "end_time": 499631.0,
      "text": "defined by redemption, growth and love."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 500543.0,
      "end_time": 503500.0,
      "text": "But what makes people change their stories?"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 503545.0,
      "end_time": 505473.0,
      "text": "Some people get help from a therapist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 505497.0,
      "end_time": 507307.0,
      "text": "but you can do it on your own, too,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 507331.0,
      "end_time": 510910.0,
      "text": "just by reflecting on your life thoughtfully,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 510115.0,
      "end_time": 512202.0,
      "text": "how your defining experiences shaped you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 512226.0,
      "end_time": 513962.0,
      "text": "what you lost, what you gained."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 514409.0,
      "end_time": 515943.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s what Emeka did."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 516832.0,
      "end_time": 518878.0,
      "text": "You won&#39;t change your story overnight;"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 518902.00000000006,
      "end_time": 521247.00000000006,
      "text": "it could take years and be painful."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 521270.0,
      "end_time": 524204.0,
      "text": "After all, we&#39;ve all suffered, and we all struggle."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 524777.0,
      "end_time": 529116.0,
      "text": "But embracing those painful memories can lead to new insights and wisdom,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 529140.0,
      "end_time": 532205.0,
      "text": "to finding that good that sustains you."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 534404.0,
      "end_time": 538937.0,
      "text": "Belonging, purpose, transcendence, storytelling:"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 539683.0,
      "end_time": 542414.0,
      "text": "those are the four pillars of meaning."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 543446.0,
      "end_time": 545520.0,
      "text": "When I was younger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 545760.0,
      "end_time": 548714.0,
      "text": "I was lucky enough to be surrounded by all of the pillars."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 549201.0,
      "end_time": 553741.0,
      "text": "My parents ran a Sufi meetinghouse from our home in Montreal."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 554506.0,
      "end_time": 558988.0,
      "text": "Sufism is a spiritual practice associated with the whirling dervishes"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 559130.0,
      "end_time": 560406.0,
      "text": "and the poet Rumi."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 561250.0,
      "end_time": 563825.0,
      "text": "Twice a week, Sufis would come to our home"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 563849.0,
      "end_time": 567609.0,
      "text": "to meditate, drink Persian tea, and share stories."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 568290.0,
      "end_time": 570986.0,
      "text": "Their practice also involved serving all of creation"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 571100.0,
      "end_time": 572819.0,
      "text": "through small acts of love,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 572844.0,
      "end_time": 576185.0,
      "text": "which meant being kind even when people wronged you."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 576209.0,
      "end_time": 579363.0,
      "text": "But it gave them a purpose: to rein in the ego."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 580732.0,
      "end_time": 583348.0,
      "text": "Eventually, I left home for college"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 583372.0,
      "end_time": 587740.0,
      "text": "and without the daily grounding of Sufism in my life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 587980.0,
      "end_time": 588685.0,
      "text": "I felt unmoored."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 588710.0,
      "end_time": 592298.0,
      "text": "And I started searching for those things that make life worth living."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 592322.0,
      "end_time": 594435.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s what set me on this journey."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 594832.0,
      "end_time": 596589.0,
      "text": "Looking back, I now realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 596613.0,
      "end_time": 599855.0,
      "text": "that the Sufi house had a real culture of meaning."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 599879.0,
      "end_time": 602385.0,
      "text": "The pillars were part of the architecture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 602409.0,
      "end_time": 605635.0,
      "text": "and the presence of the pillars helped us all live more deeply."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 606234.0,
      "end_time": 608555.0,
      "text": "Of course, the same principle applies"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 608579.0,
      "end_time": 610780.0,
      "text": "in other strong communities as well --"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 610804.0,
      "end_time": 612826.0,
      "text": "good ones and bad ones."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 613376.0,
      "end_time": 615405.0,
      "text": "Gangs, cults:"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 615429.0,
      "end_time": 618442.0,
      "text": "these are cultures of meaning that use the pillars"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 618466.0,
      "end_time": 621844.0,
      "text": "and give people something to live and die for."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 621868.0,
      "end_time": 624735.0,
      "text": "But that&#39;s exactly why we as a society"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 624759.0,
      "end_time": 626868.0,
      "text": "must offer better alternatives."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 626892.0,
      "end_time": 630643.0,
      "text": "We need to build these pillars within our families and our institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 630667.0,
      "end_time": 633249.0,
      "text": "to help people become their best selves."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 634344.0,
      "end_time": 636930.0,
      "text": "But living a meaningful life takes work."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 636954.0,
      "end_time": 638829.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s an ongoing process."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 638853.0,
      "end_time": 642582.0,
      "text": "As each day goes by, we&#39;re constantly creating our lives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 642606.0,
      "end_time": 644175.0,
      "text": "adding to our story."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 644651.0,
      "end_time": 647400.0,
      "text": "And sometimes we can get off track."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 648182.0,
      "end_time": 650930.0,
      "text": "Whenever that happens to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 650117.0,
      "end_time": 653506.0,
      "text": "I remember a powerful experience I had with my father."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 655641.0,
      "end_time": 658288.0,
      "text": "Several months after I graduated from college,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 658312.0,
      "end_time": 662170.0,
      "text": "my dad had a massive heart attack that should have killed him."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 662853.0,
      "end_time": 666670.0,
      "text": "He survived, and when I asked him what was going through his mind"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 666910.0,
      "end_time": 667713.0,
      "text": "as he faced death,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 667737.0,
      "end_time": 670420.0,
      "text": "he said all he could think about was needing to live"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 670444.0,
      "end_time": 672582.0,
      "text": "so he could be there for my brother and me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 672606.0,
      "end_time": 675195.0,
      "text": "and this gave him the will to fight for life."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 675883.0,
      "end_time": 679181.0,
      "text": "When he went under anesthesia for emergency surgery,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 679205.0,
      "end_time": 681535.0,
      "text": "instead of counting backwards from 10,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 681559.0,
      "end_time": 684728.0,
      "text": "he repeated our names like a mantra."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 685610.0,
      "end_time": 689421.0,
      "text": "He wanted our names to be the last words he spoke on earth"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 689445.0,
      "end_time": 690670.0,
      "text": "if he died."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 692853.0,
      "end_time": 696464.0,
      "text": "My dad is a carpenter and a Sufi."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 697500.0,
      "end_time": 698552.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a humble life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 698576.0,
      "end_time": 699845.0,
      "text": "but a good life."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 700384.0,
      "end_time": 704296.0,
      "text": "Lying there facing death, he had a reason to live:"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 704320.0,
      "end_time": 705728.0,
      "text": "love."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 705752.0,
      "end_time": 708203.0,
      "text": "His sense of belonging within his family,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 708227.0,
      "end_time": 709956.0,
      "text": "his purpose as a dad,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 709980.0,
      "end_time": 712994.0,
      "text": "his transcendent meditation, repeating our names --"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 713180.0,
      "end_time": 715799.0,
      "text": "these, he says, are the reasons why he survived."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 715823.0,
      "end_time": 718262.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s the story he tells himself."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 719567.0,
      "end_time": 721717.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s the power of meaning."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 722463.0,
      "end_time": 725255.0,
      "text": "Happiness comes and goes."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 725279.0,
      "end_time": 727128.0,
      "text": "But when life is really good"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 727152.0,
      "end_time": 729410.0,
      "text": "and when things are really bad,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 729610.0,
      "end_time": 732114.0,
      "text": "having meaning gives you something to hold on to."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 732142.0,
      "end_time": 733366.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 733390.0,
      "end_time": 736972.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}